class Solution {
    public boolean isPrefixString(String s, String[] words) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (String word : words) {
            sb.append(word);
            if (sb.toString().equals(s)) return true;
            if (sb.length() > s.length()) return false;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n*m)
space complexity: O(n*m)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the words array, concatenating each word to a StringBuilder and checking if the resulting string matches the target string s or exceeds its length.
